Bake pastry shells according to package directions. Slice pork into very thin strips. Mix cornstarch, broth and soy. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Add pork and stir-fry until browned. Remove pork. Heat remaining oil in skillet. Add vegetables, garlic powder and ginger. Stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp. Add cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens. Return pork to skillet and heat through. Serve in pastry shells.